{"id":"a2eee136-621c-4052-8dc3-f3d45d7d7358","title":"1509/05/08","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"24614165-e184-44a8-b260-bb58fc943ce4","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"8th May. The papal soldiers sacked Berzighella and slew many and took many prisoners, even women. ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"3ec36359-115c-4f5e-ac6b-1350bb8c362f","type":"codex/time-reference","start":0,"end":6,"value":"680e9976-1803-4fe9-adb5-1323d53c26f4","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"3a06911f-548e-44ee-8178-8752ed5e9d38","type":"style/superscript","start":1,"end":2,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d4f3de55-1735-4bc7-85b7-9ec12db8f363","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":13,"end":26,"value":"79b96672-b37a-4438-b2ce-25127990bae1","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|0|name|The papal soldiers","1|name|The papal soldiers"]},{"id":"1aca8f10-c98d-49d3-951a-f611d95b1cf0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":35,"end":45,"value":"3b98700c-933e-4da0-9fd9-bcf08221c65d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|0|name|Berzighella","1|name|Berzighella"]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"bd7bd78f-4fdf-404e-98e7-07cb73f1c392","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"","standoffProperties":[],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"6a08e295-0a0f-47f1-92bc-c12482b95f5d","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"During this time Pisa was very closely besieged, and the inhabitants fared badly. Every day, however, one heard things which showed their obstinacy \u2014 amongst others this: A woman of Pisa came out of the city with her two children and went before the commissary, saying that she was dying of hunger, and had left her mother in Pisa who was almost famished; and the commissary ordered that bread should be given her for herself and her mother and children. Going back into Pisa with the bread, she told her mother, who was ill from want of food, and on seeing the white bread, the old woman said: Che pane e questo? (What bread is this?); and when her daughter told her that she had had it outside, from the Florentines, the old woman cried: Portate via el pane de\u0027 maladetti Fiorentini; voglio prima morire! (Take away the bread of the accursed Florentines  I had rather die!); and she would not touch it. Think what hate the poor people bore to this city, finding their lot so hard, without fault of theirs. Oh, what grievous sin it is to command that there should be a war! Woe to him who is the cause of it! I pray God to forgive us; although this enterprise of ours is undertaken\u00A0legitimately: think what is the sin of those who go to war without a legitimate cause!  ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"fddc833e-222d-47d5-80e1-69782ff9263e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":17,"end":20,"value":"126d51c8-459f-4f14-af29-5970ffc7fc16","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|name|Pisa"]},{"id":"16f72f11-e30c-425f-91f7-0f079efcdec8","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":57,"end":67,"value":"6cf8914f-54ba-4767-989e-a12caccb51a0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|0|name|The inhabitants of Pisa","1|name|The inhabitants of Pisa"]},{"id":"ff637569-ddf4-45d2-b5db-3c27deeb1ea0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":132,"end":136,"value":"6cf8914f-54ba-4767-989e-a12caccb51a0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"eb97d56f-1e89-4059-a2e3-42ea6fabff04","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":173,"end":177,"value":"226e5589-573b-4e22-922f-c26c13daa6d1","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["0|0|name|A woman of Pisa who came out of the city with her two children","1|name|A woman of Pisa who came out of the city with her two children"]},{"id":"a9af3513-c13e-49b5-b8b2-082559ab539b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":179,"end":180,"value":"6d442f74-c87c-40e0-ad25-afdeac16dd11","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"b0ad4219-f4d5-4b23-a8e9-42ac849e87a6","type":"codex/meta-relation-reference","start":179,"end":185,"value":"6dca4fb0-96f0-4354-a74c-99e8a07fb27d","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"02d8bdd1-e37f-4e7b-b165-a65e12db7643","type":"codex/entity-reference",